sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant Gateway as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(PII, regex, etc.)
    participant LLM as vLLM / LLM Backend

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 1: Non-Streaming Chat Completion with Detection

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization header, stream: false
    Note over Gateway: Inject detector config<br/>from route definition
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>Forwarded Authorization + x-forwarded-* headers<br/>Optional mTLS
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run configured detectors<br/>(input detection)
    Orchestrator->>LLM: Generate chat completion
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run configured detectors<br/>(output detection)
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: JSON response with detections<br/>Optional mTLS
    Note over Gateway: If detections found &<br/>fallback_message configured:<br/>replace content with fallback
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (OpenAI-compatible)

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 2: Streaming Chat Completion with Detection (SSE)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization header, stream: true
    Note over Gateway: Inject detector config<br/>from route definition
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>Forwarded Authorization + x-forwarded-* headers<br/>Optional mTLS, streaming
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run configured detectors
    Orchestrator->>LLM: Generate chat completion (streaming)
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: SSE byte stream<br/>Optional mTLS
    Note over Gateway: Process SSE chunks,<br/>apply fallback on detection
    Gateway-->>Client: SSE (text/event-stream)
